General.Name: Lauritz.com A/S
General.Description: Lauritz.com Group A/S provides online auction services. The company offers art, design, antiquities, and home luxury products through its website. Its product categories comprising carpets, rugs, textiles; cars and boats; clothing, shoes, and accessories; electronics; furniture; glass, porcelain, and ceramics; hobby and collectibles; home and garden; hunting, fishing, arms, and militaria; jewelry; lamps and lighting; painting and sculptures; silver, bronze, copper, and pewter; sport and leisure; travel; watches and clocks; and wine and spirits. The company serves trendsetters, pensioners, students, and top executives. It has 12 auction houses. The company was incorporated in 1885 and is headquartered in Søborg, Denmark. Lauritz.com Group A/S is a subsidiary of Blixtz Holding A/S.
